content.text:
Traffic Analytics
Explore competitors’ website traffic stats, discover growth points, and amplify your marketing strategy
Register to view 10 Traffic Overview reports per day
Register (Free)
or
Log in
Get competitive insights with our website traffic checker
Discover traffic metrics for any website. Set benchmarks. Spot trends.
Engagement metrics
Track website visits, purchase conversions, and other user engagement metrics.
Daily and Weekly Data
View data on a daily, weekly, monthly, or quarterly scale.
Take Advantage of the Trend
Analyze spikes and dips in traffic to inform your next move.
Get full competitive research coverage

Set your marketing strategies for maximum impact with all-encompassing competitive intel and website traffic analysis.

Check website traffic by geo (country and subcontinent)

Unwrap the most promising markets and gather user data for location based promos.

Unwrap traffic stats for various subdomains

Compare website statistics for regional versions of competitor sites.

Perform bulk web traffic analysis

Check competitors’ and potential partners’ site traffic in one go (up to 100 sites).

Gain an edge over your competition with all-around traffic insights

Explore competitors’ website traffic stats, discover growth points, and expand your market share.

Register to view 10 Traffic Overview reports per day
Register (Free)
or
Log in
Example:
amazon.comlinkedin.comweather.com
Frequently Asked Questions
How do we get website traffic data? Do we comply with security and privacy policy?
Traffic Analytics’ insights are based on petabytes of clickstream data that comes from multiple proprietary and 3rd party data sources. Semrush’s proprietary AI algorithm accumulates, cleans, and processes the raw data, giving you an accurate view of online journeys and online activity of over 200 million real but anonymized internet users.

Learn more about traffic data in the article How Semrush Turns Traffic Data Into Traffic Intelligence.
How do I check traffic to my website?
Why does Traffic Analytic return limited or no data for some websites?
Why are different traffic values shown in Domain Analytics and Traffic Analytics?
